Using part1 init and recommender function make group member recommendations lists. Using these full lists and considering
only top50 predicted movies from each users we build a candidate list of movies for the sqeuntial recommendations.

The new method modifies the Motley method by incrementally adding elements to the result set R from
sorted candidate set S, if the element increases the F-score of the set R by treshold theta.
The first element chosen is the highest predicted movie on average. It is crucial to set the lambda
factor in F-score to represent wanted balance between similarity and diversity. Also selecting
theta will affect how eagerly the method selects similar items vs. diverse items. The default
values are: lambda=0.5 and theta=0.3.

The method increses the F-score of the result set directly. One can choose a target F-score and
use the theta-value to achieve the target if it is possible with the candidate set S.
Optimizing the result or F-score is not guaranteed. 

The program should be run in the folder where the MovieLens data FOLDER is in. The program reads
csv file with path "./ml-100k/u.*". The projectpart1.py file should be in the same folder than
the main file projectpart3.py file. The projectpart1.py file is used to build the initial group
recommendation and to read the data.

working directory
--part3
----projectpart1.py
----projectpart3.py
--ml-100k
----u.*
----...

So in working directory/root run: python .\part3\projectpart3.py